<H3> <TI>   Norwegian Deputy Speaker Meets Deng Xiaoping's Son </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Norwegian Deputy Speaker Meets Deng Xiaoping's Son </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0406033094 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0406 
GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0406033094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stockholm, 1 Jun (XINHUA) -- Edward Klimosta [name 
as received], vice president of the Norwegian Parliament, met 
Deng Pufang, president of the Chinese Federation for the 
Disabled, in Oslo on the afternoon of 1 June. The latter is on 
a visit to Norway. 
  Deng Pufang briefed Klimosta on China's development of 
services for the disabled. Both sides signaled a willingness to 
increase cooperation between their countries in expanding 
services for the disabled, and to make joint efforts to draw the 
international community's attention to issues regarding the 
disabled. 
  At the invitation of the Norwegian Social Affairs Ministry, 
the Chinese Federation for the Disabled delegation, led by Deng 
Pufang, arrived in Oslo on 31 May for a five-day goodwill visit 
to Norway. The delegation had visited Sweden prior to its 
arrival. 

