<H3> <TI>   Domestic Northwest Airlines Flight Crashes Near Xian </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Domestic Northwest Airlines Flight Crashes Near Xian </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Foreigners Said Among Dead </H4>

<F P=102> HK0606060694 Hong Kong AFP in English 0547 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> HK0606060694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 6 (AFP)--A Chinese Northwest Airlines 
plane carrying 159 people crashed Monday morning near the 
central tourist city of Xian, a spokesman from the Civil 
Aviation Administration of China said. 
  Domestic flight WH2303 from Xian in Shaanxi province to 
Guangzhou in southern Guangdong province took off at 8:12 a.m. 
(0012 GMT) and lost radio contact with Xian airport eight 
minutes later, the official said. 
  The plane was carrying 13 crew and 146 passengers, including 
foreigners, he said. 
  According to aviation sources in Guangzhou, all passengers 
aboard the Soviet-built plane were killed. 

</TEXT>

