<H3> <TI>   Finance Ministry To Issue Samurai Bonds in Tokyo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Finance Ministry To Issue Samurai Bonds in Tokyo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0306132994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1309 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0306132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 3 (XINHUA) -- China's Ministry of 
Finance is preparing to issue Samurai bonds for the first time 
in Japan, according to ministry sources. 
  The bonds will be in different terms and be issued "very 
soon", said an official who declined to give the total amount or 
to elaborate. 
  But he disclosed that Daiwa Securities Co. Ltd and Nomura 
Securities Co. Ltd will act as lead managers for the issue. 
  China's Ministry of Finance returned to international 
capital 
markets in 1993, after an absence of six years, marked by 
issuing 30 billion Japanese yen in Eurobonds on the London 
market in September and Dragon bonds totalling 300 million U.S. 
dollars in Asia in October. 
  In February this year, it successfully issued one billion 
U.S. dollar Global bonds, the biggest issue ever carried out by 
the ministry. 

</TEXT>

