<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, June 3 (XINHUA) -- The Hangzhou City 
People's Procuratorate instituted a prosecution here today 
against three accused in the case of the boat-fire tragedy which 
claimed the lives of 32 people, including 24 Taiwan tourists, in 
east China's Zhejiang Province. 
  Public trial of the case will be handled soon by the 
Hangzhou 
City Intermediate People's Court. 
  A collegiate bench has been formed by the Hangzhou City 
Intermediate People's Court, in accordance with the law. Copies 
of the indictment have been sent to the three accused -- Wu 
Lihong, Hu Zhihan and Yu Aijun. 
  On March 31, the pleasure boat "Hairui" was set ablaze on 
Qiandao Lake in Zhejiang Province. No one aboard survived. 

