<F P=101> East Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Tells Hungarians No Reason To Extend NATO </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Tells Hungarians No Reason To Extend NATO </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1504083694 Budapest MTI in English 1840 GMT 14 Apr 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1504083694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 14 April (MTI) -- A senior official at the 
Chinese Foreign Ministry, anonymously told MTI's Beijing 
correspondent that he saw no reason for the expansion of NATO, 
now the Warsaw Pact organization has broken up. 
  The official made the remark in answer to a question on the 
Chinese Government position on the integration of Hungary and 
other Central European countries into NATO, and a possible 
eastward expansion of the North-Atlantic organization. 
  This was the first time that a senior Chinese source had 
taken a stand on the issue. 
  At a press conference held in Beijing for Central and 
Eastern 
European correspondents, the same senior official said China 
understood Hungary's desire to become a full member of the 
European Union and this way strengthen its links with other 
European states. 
  However, the Chinese Government hopes Hungary will not 
forget 
about its eastern links while integrating into Europe, he added. 

</TEXT>

