<H3> <TI>   CPC Calls on Cadres To Maintain Social Stability </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CPC Calls on Cadres To Maintain Social Stability </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0606064294 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 4 Jun 94 
Morning Edition p 5 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0606064294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Hiroyuki Sugiyama] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 3 Jun -- A Chinese source has disclosed 
that, on the eve of the fifth anniversary of the Tiananmen 
incident, the CPC issued in mid-May an internal notice for 
cadres with instructions that every effort should be made to 
maintain stability in their own respective units. 
  A strong dissatisfaction against society has been noted 
among 
those on low incomes such as workers at state-run enterprises 
and peasants. This feeling has been considerably intensified 
because of the growing disparity in incomes, inflation, and 
corruption among cadres. 
  It is reported that while the notice frankly admits the 
situation exists, it also points out that "all cadres should try 
to understand the issue correctly, and at the same time be 
confident it will be eventually settled by the party." 
  In this way, the CPC has once again called on its cadres to 
trust the party. The notice can be said to indicate the current 
situation in which the sense of crisis within the party has been 
intensified by factors such as disparity in income, inflation, 
and corruption, which have caused social instability and now 
apply strong pressure on the party. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

